# Sindri — `main` branch

`main` carries no product source. It hosts:

- Umbrella `README.md` (version router) and `CHANGELOG.md` (umbrella).
- Repo-wide governance: `LICENSE`, `SECURITY.md`, `CONTRIBUTING.md`, `CODEOWNERS`, `dependabot.yml`.
- Centralized `.github/workflows/` that triggers on push/PR to `v1`/`v2`/`v3`/`v4`.
- Governance docs in `docs/` (`RELEASE.md`, `CHANGELOG_MANAGEMENT.md`, `COMPARISON_GUIDE.md`).

## Where work happens

| Branch | Stack | Status |
|---|---|---|
| `v1` | legacy bash | EOL — security-only |
| `v2` | Bash + Docker | Maintenance |
| `v3` | Rust workspace | Active |
| `v4` | Rust, redesigned | Pre-release |

For stack-specific guidance, switch to the relevant branch and read its `CLAUDE.md`.

## Working on `main`

- Do not add product code here.
- Workflow files live under `.github/workflows/`. Each `ci-vN.yml` triggers only on its own `v*` branch.
- Reusable callables are prefixed with `_` (e.g. `_ci-rust.yml`, `_ci-bash.yml`).
- See `.github/WORKFLOW_ARCHITECTURE.md` for the routing model.
